From: uknf@rzstud1.rz.uni-karlsruhe.de (Olaf Titz)
Subject: Re: CGA SNOW ... Any Thoughts ?
Date: 7 Sep 1993 14:37:04 GMT

In article <26g181$51c@news1.digex.net>,
Mike Rice <rice@access.digex.net> wrote:

> Got 'er up on a 386 built with old parts.  One of those old parts 
> was a CGA monitor ... Got the old "SNOWY" screen !  Any thoughts
> as to how to eliminate the sloppy presentation  ??

The problem is not with the screen, but rather with the antique video
card. Get a new one, CGAs or low-grade VGAs cost almost nothing these
days. 

You could probably fix the problem in software (prefix every access to
video RAM in the kernel with a wait for retrace), but that isn't worth
the effort, IMHO.

Olaf
